HEADWORD: Mulatto
<hw>Mu*lat"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Mulattoes</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Sp. & Pg.
<ets>mulato</ets>, masc., <ets>mulata</ets>, fem., of a mixed breed, fr.
<ets>mulo</ets> mule, L. <ets>mulus</ets>. See <er>Mule</er>.]</ety>
<def>The offspring of a negress by a white man, or of a white woman by a
negro, -- usually of a brownish yellow complexion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mulattress</ent>⟦br⟧
